"Here is a Java method to convert a string to title case, while handling exceptions for certain words:

```java
public class TitleCaseConverter {
    private static final String[] EXCEPTION_WORDS = {"of", "the", "is", "and"};

    public static String convertToTitleCase(String input) {
        if (input == null || input.isEmpty()) {
            return input;
        }

        // Capitalize the first letter
        char firstChar = input.charAt(0);
        if (firstChar >= 'a' && firstChar <= 'z') {
            input = Character.toUpperCase(firstChar) + input.substring(1);
        }

        // Process each word
        String[] words = input.split("\\s+");
        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = 0; i < words.length; i++) {
            String word = words[i];
            boolean isException = false;

            for (String exception : EXCEPTION_WORDS) {
                if (word.equals(exception)) {
                    isException = true;
                    break;
                }
            }

            if (!isException) {
                // Capitalize the word if it is not an exception word
                result.append(Character.toUpperCase(word.charAt(0)));
                result.append(word.substring(1));
            } else {
                result.append(word);
            }

            if (i < words.length - 1) {
                result.append(" ");
            }
        }

        return result.toString();
    }
}
```

